@davatron5000 I have a 5 min video explaining how screen readers work curated and presented by 2 blind guys that I'm happy to share. They use a thought provoking use case of trying to apply for a job to provide an example of the friction they experience.

I also have 2 min video of someone with low vision explaining magnification.

Sing out if you'd like me to share.

@WilcoFiers @straker 
I would like to help with this fix - would the change be needed to `isNativelyFocusable` in https://github.com/dequelabs/axe-core/blob/develop/lib/commons/dom/is-natively-focusable.js#L13, to also handle `audio` and `video` elements ? If yes, simillar to the check for `href`, for `a` and `area` elements, would we need to check for the presence of the `controls` attribute ?

First-time contributing to `axe-core`, so would greatly appreciate your guidance.

@WilcoFiers @straker
Hope you are doing great ?

Following up on above - please let me know, in case the above approach doesn't sound right, will look further.
